<recipe>
<title>
Mexican Macaroni and Cheese
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 lb . lean ground beef
1 (10 oz.) can Rotel (I used the mild Rotel)
1/2-1 T . taco seasoning
1 (14 oz.) can beef broth
2 c . dry elbow macaroni
4 oz . reduced-fat cream cheese , in 4 slices
1/4 c . butter
1/4 c . all-purpose flour
1 Â½ c . milk
2 c . shredded sharp cheddar cheese
Cilantro
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in Rotel (and liquid), taco seasoning, beef broth, and macaroni.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese, and stir until just melted.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in flour, and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until just bubbly.
Add the milk, and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat, and stir in cheese.
Stir the cheese sauce into the pasta mixture.
Garnish with cilantro just before serving.
</instructions>
</recipe>
